OL,3,CMore than half of teachers work at a
OL,4,Cschool where a child is homeless
OL,6,FChief executive of Shelter Sarah
OL,7,FElliott said: "The housing emergency
OL,8,Fis infiltrating our classrooms and
OL,9,Frobbing children of their most basic
OL,10,Fneed of a safe and secure home.
OL,11,FChildren shouldn't have to try and
OL,12,Fbalance their studies with the
OL,13,Fhorrific experience of homelessness.
OL,15,F"Teachers are witnessing the same
OL,16,Fdevastating effects of growing up in
OL,17,Ftemporary accommodation on children
OL,18,Fthat our services see every day."
