OL,3,CMore than half of teachers work at a
OL,4,Cschool where a child is homeless
OL,6,F56% of teachers in the South West
OL,7,Freported being aware of at least one
OL,8,Fchild who was homeless in the past
OL,9,Fyear at their school, with 35% being a
OL,10,Fchild or children who they teach or
OL,11,Finteract with and the other 21% being
OL,12,Fa child or children at their school
OL,13,Fwho they don't personally teach.
OL,15,FNASUWT chief executive Matt Wrack said
OL,16,Fthe lack of a safe and permanent home
OL,17,Fputs children's future life chances at
OL,18,Frisk.
